      <h1 class='title'>Departmental Expenditure (Department of Health and Food Standards Agency)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 28 February 2003 vol 400 cc50-2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50ws' title='Col. 50WS &mdash; HC Deb 28 February 2003 vol 400 c50WS' name='column_50ws' href='#column_50ws' rel='bookmark'>50WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0400P2_20030228_CWS_14'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alan-milburn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0400P2_20030228_CWS_14' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alan Milburn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-alan-milburn" title="Mr Alan Milburn">The Secretary of State for Health (Mr. Alan Milburn)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Subject to Parliamentary approval of the necessary Supplementary Estimate, the Department and the Food Standards Agency departmental expenditure limits (DELs) will be increased by &#x00A3;448,742,000 from &#x00A3;56,476,255,000 to &#x00A3;56,924,997,000 and the administration cost limits (ACL) will decrease by &#x00A3;10,539,000 from &#x00A3;379,782,000 to &#x00A3;369,243,000. The Department's DEL will be increased by &#x00A3;448,742,000 from &#x00A3;56,341,630,000 to &#x00A3;56,790,372,000 and the ACL will increase by &#x00A3;8,829,000 from &#x00A3;324,663,000 to &#x00A3;333,492,000. The Food Standards Agency DEL remains unchanged at &#x00A3;134,625,000 but the ACL will decrease by &#x00A3;19,368,000 from &#x00A3;55,119,000 to &#x00A3;35,751,000. The impact on resource and capital are set out in the table.</p><p>
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Resource (&#x00A3;'000)</span></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Capital (&#x00A3;'000)</span></td>
